President Cyril Ramaphosa is yet to decide on whether the 21-day lockdown will be extended. He also says the number of infections would have been much higher, had the lockdown not been initiated. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is yet to decide on whether the 21-day lockdown will be extended. He also says the number of infections would have been much higher had the lockdown not been initiated. SA lockdown: Cele not ruling out extension Ramaphosa was speaking during his visit to the Rand Water head office in Johannesburg on Tuesday afternoon. He said that the lockdown has thus far helped slow down the spread. READ: COVID-19 death toll rises to 13, confirmed cases to 1,749 "If we had not locked down South Africa as we have, I can tell you without any shadow of a doubt that the infection rate... would have been a lot, lot higher than what we have," Ramaphosa said. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.